rComments: Worst professor I have ever had at any university in the world.  Seems lazy.
Wonderful prof! Very clear and organized, and incredibly patient. Has a great sense of humour. Overall made the course very enjoyable and I would definitely recommend it to anyone.
Amazing professor! Very approachable and helpful. Explains everything well.
She is very fair and explains everything in detail.  I like her very much; she has a great personality and speaks both English and Italian extremely well.

AMAZING PROF! She's really nice & cares about her students. Really good marker, too! Her lessons, much like everyone else is saying, were very clear and the tests were very fair. She was a GREAT prof to start learning Italian with, and I WISH I had her in 250!!!
Clear, organized, and very fair..She has a great sense of humour and is very helpful..awesome prof and great class!..

A very pleasant,  easygoing and approachable instructor.  Her lectures/lessons are very comprehensive, thorough and CLEAR.  If you keep up with the coursework, you WILL get a stellar mark in her class. Her tests offer up no surprises or tricks.  Overall, EXCELLENT instructor... would definitely recommend!!

I loved this prof. at a first glance she seemed very serious and conservative but when she cracks a joke she literally kills you with laughter. I really enjoyed her course and found her to be extremely easygoing with a GREAT unsurpassed sense of humor.
good material, but not a cinema studies prof, so not particularly insightful. good tests (no surprises and do-able)
Her lectures are very clear and easy to follow and the tests are straightforward with no surprises. Super-nice, too!
nicest lady ever. enthusiastic, extremely helpful and approachable. Tests are easy. Lots of reading but it is all worth it and all easy reading. Take this course!!
She should not be teaching Italian with that horrible (Meridonale + Canadian mix) accent. UofT needs a real Italian teacher, someone who is from where real Italian is spoken. Shame on her.
She never once let us out early!!
Italian course in Siena: Great prof for languages - very friendly, encouraging, and approachable.
Very approachable and friendly.  Excellent selection of films for the first term.  Repetetive during lectures, however.  Also, not a film scholar, so there is a tendancy to focus on thematics.
not a good film prof.  she repeats hersrelf.  A LOT. let us out early.
